The paper discusses the use of deep learning and neural networks for cancer pathology analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on optimizing the neural network architecture for speed and accuracy suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of HPC systems and software stack for neural architecture search suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
